H. J. RYAN, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. THE PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE, UNITED STATES CONGRESS, Defendant-Appellee. No. 15069. United States Court of Appeals Sixth Circuit. Feb. 22, 1963. H. J. Ryan, plaintiff-appellant, in pro. per. Carrol D. Kilgore, Asst. U. S. Atty., Nashville, Tenn. (Kenneth Harwell, U. S. Atty., Nashville, Tenn., on the brief), for defendant-appellee.

Before WEICK and O’SULLIVAN, Circuit Judges, and DARR, District Judge.

ORDER.

Upon consideration of the appeal in the above case the Court finding no error in the proceedings and judgment of the District Court,

IT IS ORDERED that the judgment be affirmed.
